    "PREPARATION FOR THE MINOR TIM 50: Business Information Systems TIM 58: Systems Analysis and Design CSE 20: Introduction to Programming in Python OR CSE 30: Programming Abstractions: Python Plus one of the following calculus sequences: AM 11A: Mathematical Methods for Economists I AND AM 11B: Mathematical Methods for Economists II MATH 11A: Calculus with Applications AND MATH 11B: Calculus with Applications MATH 19A: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics AND MATH 19B: Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics Please visit the Baskin Engineering Undergraduate Experience website to learn more about this minor.",
    "UC Santa Cruz students may choose to complete one or more minors, provided they can finish all required coursework within their maximum enrollment terms and allowable credits. While a minor will appear on a student's official transcript, it will not be listed on their diploma. Pursuing a minor is a personal decision that should align with a student's educational and career goals. Students do not apply for minors when submitting their application to UC Santa Cruz. After enrolling, transfer students interested in pursuing a minor should contact the department offering the minor for guidance."
